<whdroplet name="drDemoSetupfire">
<ol>
<li> Interbase Objects is used to connect from Delphi to Firebird.
Compiles with IBObjects versions 4.8.6, 4.9.5 and 4.9.9, with D07 through D14. Note that WebHub v2.125+ is required for use with 
D12 and D14.</li>
<li> 
<whtranslation key="~whDemoSetupfire" lingvo="eng">
We installed Firebird SQL server v1.5.3 on demos.href.com using the <b>Official Windows Setup</b>. <![CDATA[<a target="_blank" href="http://www.ibphoenix.com/main.nfs?a=ibphoenix&page=ibp_download_15">download</a>]]>.  Firebird SQL is an open source database. Firebird runs on both Windows and Linux servers.
</whtranslation>
</li>
<li>We used the employee.gdb file, distributed by Borland, CodeGear and Embarcadero Software with various versions of Delphi since 1994.</li>
<li>We set up a Firebird ALIAS named "employee" pointing to this gdb file.  The entry in alias.conf looks like this
<pre>
employee = c:\BorlandSampleDB\employee.gdb
</pre></li>
</ol>

